<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>PipelineStoppedException on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/pipelinestoppedexception/</link><description>Recent content in PipelineStoppedException on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/pipelinestoppedexception/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] PowerShell PipelineStoppedException</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/powershell-pipeline-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/powershell-pipeline-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="powershell-pipelinestoppedexception-fix"&gt;PowerShell PipelineStoppedException Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PipelineStoppedException occurs when a pipeline is interrupted by a terminating error, &lt;code&gt;throw&lt;/code&gt; statement, or Ctrl+C cancellation. It propagates through the pipeline and may mask the original error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PowerShell pipelines process data through a chain of cmdlets. When one cmdlet throws a terminating error, the pipeline stops and all pending operations are cancelled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Terminating error in a pipeline cmdlet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ErrorActionPreference = &amp;quot;Stop&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt; converting errors to terminating&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explicit &lt;code&gt;throw&lt;/code&gt; in pipeline code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;User pressed Ctrl+C during pipeline execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pipeline timeout&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-catch-terminating-errors-in-pipeline"&gt;1. Catch terminating errors in pipeline&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Use try/catch around pipeline&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Get-Content file.txt | ForEach-Object {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Process that might throw&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $_ | ConvertFrom-Json
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;PipelineStoppedException&lt;/span&gt;] {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Write-Warning &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Pipeline was stopped&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Write-Warning &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error: &lt;/span&gt;$_&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-use--erroraction-for-non-terminating-errors"&gt;2. Use -ErrorAction for non-terminating errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Continue on errors&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-Content file.txt -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or warn and continue&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-Content file.txt -ErrorAction &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Continue&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-avoid-erroractionpreference--stop-in-pipelines"&gt;3. Avoid $ErrorActionPreference = &amp;ldquo;Stop&amp;rdquo; in pipelines&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# This makes ALL errors terminating&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ErrorActionPreference = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Stop&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Use per-cmdlet error action instead&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-Content file.txt -ErrorAction Stop
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-use-break-to-stop-pipeline-intentionally"&gt;4. Use break to stop pipeline intentionally&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Break exits the current scope&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;.100&lt;/span&gt; | ForEach-Object {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($_ &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-eq&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;50&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;break&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $_
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="invalid-operation"&gt;InvalidOperation&lt;/a&gt; — operation errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="powershell-parameter-binding"&gt;ParameterBindingException&lt;/a&gt; — parameter issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="powershell-job-error"&gt;Job Failed Error&lt;/a&gt; — background job errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PowerShell PipelineStoppedException Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/powershell-pipeline-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/powershell-pipeline-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="powershell-pipelinestoppedexception-error-fix"&gt;PowerShell PipelineStoppedException Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A PowerShell pipeline error occurs when the pipeline is stopped by an exception, typically due to a terminating error in a pipeline command.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;PipelineStoppedException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a pipeline is forcefully stopped, usually because a cmdlet threw a terminating error. This propagates through the pipeline and stops all downstream commands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Terminating error in pipeline command&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manual pipeline stop via &lt;code&gt;$host.SetShouldExit()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nested pipeline with unhandled exceptions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pipeline broken by Write-Error with -ErrorAction Stop&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-handle-errors-in-pipeline"&gt;1. Handle errors in pipeline&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Use try-catch in pipeline&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Get-Content &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -ErrorAction Stop |
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ForEach-Object { $_.ToUpper() } |
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Out-File &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;output.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;System.IO.FileNotFoundException&lt;/span&gt;] {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Write-Warning &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Input file not found&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Write-Warning &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Pipeline error: &lt;/span&gt;$($_.Exception.Message)&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-use--erroraction-appropriately"&gt;2. Use -ErrorAction appropriately&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Control error propagation&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-Content &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Where-Object { $_ &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-match&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;pattern&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; } |
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ForEach-Object { Write-Output $_ }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-break-pipeline-safely"&gt;3. Break pipeline safely&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Check before processing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$results = @()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-Content &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; | ForEach-Object {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($_ &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-eq&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;STOP&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Exit ForEach, don&amp;#39;t break pipeline&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $results += $_.ToUpper()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-use-try-catch-for-nested-pipelines"&gt;4. Use try-catch for nested pipelines&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Wrap complex pipelines&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $data = Get-ChildItem &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;C:\logs&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -Filter &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;*.log&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -ErrorAction Stop
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $data | Sort-Object Length -Descending |
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Select-Object -First &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt; |
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ForEach-Object { Write-Host $_.Name }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Write-Warning &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error accessing logs: &lt;/span&gt;$($_.Exception.Message)&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="powershell-job-error-v2"&gt;PowerShell Job Error&lt;/a&gt; — background job failures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="powershell-workflow-error-v2"&gt;PowerShell Workflow Error&lt;/a&gt; — workflow errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="powershell-module-load-error"&gt;PowerShell Module Load Error&lt;/a&gt; — module issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PowerShell PipelineStoppedException Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/pipeline-failed/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/pipeline-failed/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="powershell-pipelinestoppedexception-fix"&gt;PowerShell PipelineStoppedException Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a running pipeline is stopped before all commands have completed. The error message reads: &lt;code&gt;PipelineStoppedException: The pipeline has been stopped.&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PowerShell pipelines stream data between commands. If an upstream command fails, is interrupted by the user, or throws a terminating error, the entire pipeline is stopped. Downstream commands receive this exception when they attempt to read from the pipeline after it has been halted.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>